## Independent reproduction of the reported bug (before writing any test)

```
$ npm pack --pack-destination /tmp/pack-verify && cd /tmp/pack-verify \
  && tar xzf blockrun-cli-1.2.0.tgz && cd package && node dist/index.js --version
Error: cost-model: could not locate src/commands/ from /private/tmp/pack-verify/package/dist
    at findCommandsDir (file:///.../dist/index.js:3375:9)
    at deriveCostModel (file:///.../dist/index.js:3378:15)
Node.js v25.6.1
exit=1
```
Confirms team-lead's report exactly: EVERY command (including `--version`, which
doesn't even touch cost-model logically) crashes, because `cost-model.ts`'s
`COMMAND_COST_MODEL = deriveCostModel()` runs at MODULE TOP LEVEL, and `commands
-catalog.ts` (imported by `index.ts`) imports `cost-model.js` unconditionally — the
throw happens before `program.parseAsync()` is ever reached.

